description.narrative: Government and partners have enhanced capacity to generate demand for quality education through advocacy, sustained behaviour change and social protection, which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change (Covid), Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation, Partnerships And Engagement: Public And Private, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Business and Key Business Stakeholders demonstrate growing willingness, commitment and resource allocation for protecting and promoting child rights in policy and practice by 2022

title.narrative: Government and partners have enhanced capacity to generate demand for quality education through advocacy, sustained behaviourchange and social protection

description.narrative: State school education departments supported by UNICEF for school reopening with ‘back to school’ communication in 12 states (Assam, Andhra Pradesh, Bihar, Chhattisgarh, Jharkhand, Gujarat, Madhya Pradesh, Maharashtra, Odisha, Rajasthan, West Bengal, Uttar Pradesh). Simultaneously, about 10 million parents were regularly engaged on supporting learning at home via networks- self-help groups, community volunteers, adolescent collectives, online platforms, television, and community radio. 100,000 school management committees (SMCs) capacitated on their role, responsibilities, participation in school management in Jharkhand, Rajasthan, UP. More than USD 4 million leveraged for responsive parenting, SMC capacity building. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:09/01/2022
